Give a brief history of the internet 
The internet was invented in the late 1960s by a group of researchers at the University of California, Los Angeles (UCLA). It was originally called ARPANET and was designed to allow researchers to share information and communicate with each other. Over time, the internet grew and evolved into the global network we know today, with billions of users worldwide accessing a vast array of information and services.

Describe to me some good coding practices 
Some good coding practices include: 

1. Properly commenting code to make it easier to understand and maintain. 
2. Using consistent naming conventions for variables, functions, and classes. 
3. Writing clean and readable code that is easy to debug. 
4. Avoiding unnecessary complexity and keeping code simple and concise. 
5. Using version control to track changes and revert mistakes. 
6. Testing code thoroughly before deploying it. 
7. Keeping up-to-date with industry standards and best practices. 
8. Collaborating with other developers

describe the geographic location of London in UK
London is located in the southeast of England, on the River Thames. It is the capital city of the United Kingdom and the largest city in Europe.

describe the geographic location of Toronto in Canada
Toronto is located in the province of Ontario, Canada. It is situated on the northwestern shore of Lake Ontario, and is the largest city in Canada with a population of over 2.8 million people. Toronto is a multicultural city with a diverse population, and is home to many cultural events and festivals throughout the year.
